While the group was recovering (I had full life, having learned well the Evade and Backstab techniques, and with nods to the great cleric Caderlly) I did my rogueish thing, and wandered off in search of adventure.<br>
I didn't find any.<br>
Until I came to a tree near the castle.  It didn't take me long to figure out that I could climb the base of this tree, and as I turned around to jump down, I realized I had an awesome view of the Throne Room!  I was thinking of how nice it would be to pull by chucking daggers through the window, where they'd have to run straight past my group to get at me (which would then pull them off me) when I noticed the group inside was in harried battle with a bunch of Legos an Emissary, and a Royal Guard - when there on the floor was Lord Darish himself, dead and waiting for looting.<br>
So I put on my hide and sneak at the entrance to the castle (and hoped like hell the lego's were occupied by the throne room team) and snuck toward the action - <br>
They had managed to kill them all, and were backed up against the far wall behind the throne medding and healing I guess, and there was carnage all around<br>
I poked my head in the room and looked around - seeing noone nearby, I snuck in to see what nice loot Darish had on him.  <br>
And of course &quot;You may not loot this corpse at this time&quot;<br>
But I was nothing if not daring (especially considering that legos and emissaries can see through hide at level 10)and while keeping an eye out for movement, I just kept clicking.<br>
Bingo!  On Lord Darish's corpse was the fabled (again, at level 10) Dwarven Axe (6/26), so of course I, again in my good rogueish way, ganked that sucker's axe.<br>
This was one of those days that makes you love being a rogue.<br>
I can't help but smile everytime I think that somewhere there's a group, level 17-20 by now, that still tell everyone that they wouldn't believe how fast Lord Darish's body disappears after a kill!<br>
Of course, I still find it hilarious when you're hide/sneaking through a dungeon, and you hail someone, and they spin circles trying to find you<br>
<br>
Estalt - Wood Elf Rogue of the 14th purloining<br>
